Author::::Mark Jordan
DateTime::::2016-03-10T18:19:03Z
I'm certainly not being dishonest but reacting honestly to what anyone should surely admit is an appalling situation. These people are being detained, they have, in general, neither been convicted of criminal offences nor are they awaiting trial for any and, therefore, they are being held in detention without trial. You can argue that this is justified under the circumstances - many people do - but it doesn't change the nature of their incarceration. They are being held indefinitely in that, general targets notwithstanding, the have no way to know how long their case will take to process. If they have entered the country illegally it is often simply due to the case that, having fled from a war zone, they have been unable to retain the kind of paperwork which would make processing simpler. The same was true of many Jewish people fleeing the Nazis.



