The number of asylum seekers who are detained is a small percentage of those applying for asylum. They are detained because their claim has failed, or because they are awaiting deportation, or because their claim is unlikely to succeed. If you know your claim is hopeless you would be likely to abscond as you have nothing to lose.



Author::::VerneWells
DateTime::::2016-03-10T11:49:12Z
An asylum seeker is someone who applies for asylum - anyone from outside the UK can do this. When their claim fails they are a failed asylum seeker and subject to detention and deportation. An economic migrant can be an asylum seeker, as can anyone.



